# AI-assisted contributions

Follow [`docs/AI_ASSISTED_CONTRIBUTIONS.md`](../../docs/AI_ASSISTED_CONTRIBUTIONS.md) and the kernel-oriented summary at [coding-assistants.rst](https://github.com/torvalds/linux/blob/master/Documentation/process/coding-assistants.rst).

## Rules for agents

1. **Never** add `Signed-off-by`, DCO certification, or any text that implies a human legally certified the change. Only the human author may add that after review.

2. **Before proposing or drafting any commit message** (or hunk of a message the user will paste into git), **ask the user to pick one** — unless they already stated it in this turn:

   - **A — No AI for this commit:** use `Assisted-by: human-only` (or `Assisted-by: none` if they prefer).
   - **B — AI/tools assisted:** use `Assisted-by: Cursor:<model-or-agent-label>` (and optional specialized tools per [`docs/AI_ASSISTED_CONTRIBUTIONS.md`](../../docs/AI_ASSISTED_CONTRIBUTIONS.md)).

   Offer **A** and **B** as explicit choices (e.g. “Reply A or B”). After they choose, **include the matching trailer** in every commit message you suggest so CI on `main` and local habits stay consistent.

3. If the user already chose in the same conversation (e.g. “use B”), do not ask again for that commit message unless they ask for a new message.

4. Optional trailers may list **specialized** tools (not basic git/editor/compiler), matching project docs.

**Git auto-append:** Husky **`prepare-commit-msg`** picks: non-empty **`ASSISTED_BY`** → **`git config ressource.assistedBy`** → default **`Cursor:unspecified`** (no typing). For **A** (human-only), tell the user: **`git config ressource.assistedBy human-only`** for a session, or edit the line; **`git config --unset ressource.assistedBy`** restores the default. Details: [`docs/AI_ASSISTED_CONTRIBUTIONS.md`](../../docs/AI_ASSISTED_CONTRIBUTIONS.md).

When editing **policy** here or in `docs/AI_ASSISTED_CONTRIBUTIONS.md`, Husky, or CI for this check, run the **documentation-sync** skill so the checklist and [`docs/DEVELOPER_GUARDRAILS.md`](../../docs/DEVELOPER_GUARDRAILS.md) stay accurate.
